/*
 * aislopdesk_ffi.h — the C ABI of `aislopdesk-ffi`.
 *
 * GENERATED by cbindgen from the Rust `#[repr(C)]` / `extern "C"` surface in `src/`.
 * DO NOT EDIT BY HAND — regenerate via `rust/build-apple.sh`; a CI drift-gate fails on any diff.
 *
 * This header is the contract a non-Rust platform shell links against to drive the pure
 * `aislopdesk-core` codecs (Swift on Apple via a bridging header; a JNI shim on Android).
 *
 * Memory contract: every `AisdBytes` / `AisdBytesArray` / `AisdWireMessage` this library *returns*
 * owns a Rust allocation and MUST be released with the matching `aisd_*_free` — never C `free()`.
 * Buffers you pass *in* are borrowed for the call only (`cap == 0`) and never freed by Rust.
 * Opaque handles are created by `*_new` and destroyed by `*_free`; use-after-free / double-free is
 * undefined behaviour, exactly as in C. Decoders overwrite `*out` without freeing prior contents.
 *
 * C-struct booleans are `uint8_t` read as `(!= 0)` — never a Rust `bool` (validity-UB for any byte
 * other than 0/1; a JNI `jboolean` / C `int` may carry 2).
 */

